## Best Practices

### 1. Meaningful Names
Use clear, descriptive names:
```typescript
// GOOD
// #region API Request Handlers

// LESS CLEAR
// #region stuff
```

### 2. Logical Organization
Group related code:
```typescript
// #region Imports
// #region Types
// #region Components
// #region Utilities
```

### 3. Keep Region Sizes Reasonable
Use regions to organize by feature, not by individual functions:
```typescript
// GOOD - Logical grouping
// #region User Management
function getUser() { }
function createUser() { }
function deleteUser() { }
// #endregion

// LESS CLEAR - Too granular
// #region Get User
function getUser() { }
// #endregion
```

### 4. Comment Style Consistency
Use consistent comment styles within your file:
```typescript
// Good - consistent style
// #region Section 1
// #endregion

// #region Section 2
// #endregion
```

